data.name: pollingIntervalValue.ToolTip
data.value: How often WinNUT refreshes data from the NUT server.

data.name: Label3.Text
data.value: Login credentials to the Nut server (leave blank if not required)

data.name: Tb_UPS_Name.ToolTip
data.value: UPS name to monitor. Accepted Value: Name of the UPS configured in the Nut server.

data.name: Tb_Port.ToolTip
data.value: Nut Server Port Number (default = 3493). Accepted value: Numeric value from 1 to 65535.

data.name: Tb_Server_IP.ToolTip
data.value: Nut server address. Accepted value: IPV4 / IPV6 / FQDN address.

data.name: Cbx_Freq_Input.ToolTip
data.value: Sets the input frequency if not supplied by the UPS.

data.name: Tb_BattV_Max.ToolTip
data.value: Maximum Battery Voltage. Accepted value: Numeric value from 0 to 100.

data.name: Tb_OutV_Max.ToolTip
data.value: Maximum Output Voltage. Accepted value: Numeric value from 0 to 999.

data.name: Tb_InF_Max.ToolTip
data.value: Maximum input frequency. Accepted value: Numeric value from 0 to 100.

data.name: Tb_BattV_Min.ToolTip
data.value: Minimum Battery Voltage. Accepted value: Numeric value from 0 to 100.

data.name: Tb_OutV_Min.ToolTip
data.value: Minimum Output Voltage. Accepted value: Numeric value from 0 to 999.

data.name: Tb_InF_Min.ToolTip
data.value: Minimum input frequency. Accepted value: Numeric value from 0 to 100.

data.name: Tb_InV_Max.ToolTip
data.value: Maximum input voltage. Accepted value: Numeric value from 0 to 999.

data.name: Tb_InV_Min.ToolTip
data.value: Minimum input voltage. Accepted value: Numeric value from 0 to 999.

data.name: CB_Use_Logfile.ToolTip
data.value: Write logging events to a file.

data.name: CB_Systray.ToolTip
data.value: Reduced to the taskbar or Systray.

data.name: CB_Follow_FSD.ToolTip
data.value: Indicates whether a shutdown should be performed when the NUT server signals a forced shutdown (FSD = Force ShutDown)

data.name: Tb_GraceTime.ToolTip
data.value: Additional grace period limit. Accepted value: Numeric value from 0 to 3600.

data.name: Cb_ExtendTime.ToolTip
data.value: Allow additional time during the shutdown procedure. Note: This additional time could go beyond the UPS backup time - USE WITH CAUTION!!!

data.name: Tb_Delay_Stop.ToolTip
data.value: Stop procedure delay if delayed. Accepted value: Numeric value from 0 to 3600.

data.name: Cbx_TypeStop.ToolTip
data.value: Type of stop at the end of the stop procedure.

data.name: Cb_ImmediateStop.ToolTip
data.value: Starts the shutdown procedure immediately or timed.

data.name: Tb_BattLimit_Time.ToolTip
data.value: Lower backup time limit triggering the shutdown procedure. Accepted value: Numeric value from 0 to 3600.

data.name: Tb_BattLimit_Load.ToolTip
data.value: Lower limit of the battery level triggering the shutdown procedure. Accepted value: Numeric value from 0 to 100.

data.name: Cbx_Branch_Update.ToolTip
data.value: Use the Stable or Devellop branch during verification.
